2.10	Champ-de-Mars	Champ de Mars	The Champ de Mars (French pronunciation: ; English: ) is a large public greenspace in Paris, France, located in the seventh arrondissement, between the Eiffel Tower to the northwest and the Ã‰cole Militaire to the southeast. The park is named after the Campus Martius ("Mars Field") in Rome, a tribute to the Roman god of war. The name also alludes to the fact that the lawns here were formerly used as drilling and marching grounds by the French military.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/29/MG-Paris-Champ_de_Mars.jpg/250px-MG-Paris-Champ_de_Mars.jpg
